I had the hardest year of my life. I did my best in the college entrance exams but got grades I had never gotten in my entire life. It was horrible in every sense of the word.I got the results a month ago, I thought I would be happy by this time because I did my best, but I wasn't, I got what I feared was depression, I could no longer see anything good in life I don't know what to do or what lies ahead, I'm just more afraid of life, I'm afraid of failing to be the person I dreamed of being when I was little, I could hardly sleep from thinking about this every day.
Last night I found this video and played it and then my thoughts stopped and I fell into a proper sleep for the first time for a long. I'm writing this early in the morning after waking up and I really want to say that I am grateful, and I will try again..
